cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for facial landmark detection, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep convolutional and deconvolutional networks, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM) components, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
